<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idab8a15c1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s10142"><num value="10142">§ 10142.</num><heading> Ready Reserve</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idab8a15c2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s10142/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> The Ready Reserve consists of units or Reserves, or both, liable for active duty as provided in sections 12301 and 12302 of this title.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idab8a15c3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s10142/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> The authorized strength of the Ready Reserve is 2,900,000.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idab8a15c4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/103/337/dA/tXVI/s1661/a/1">Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title XVI, § 1661(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="1994-10-05">Oct. 5, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2972">108 Stat. 2972</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idab8a15c5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idab8a15c6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="idab8a15c7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s268/a">section 268(a) of this title</ref>, prior to repeal by <ref href="/us/pl/103/337/s1661/a/2/A">Pub. L. 103–337, § 1661(a)(2)(A)</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idab8a15c8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idab8a15c9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1994-12-01">Dec. 1, 1994</date>, except as otherwise provided, see <ref href="/us/pl/103/337/s1691">section 1691 of Pub. L. 103–337</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s10001">section 10001 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
